main event: A bright object was observed moving across the sky in Danville, Ohio on May 30, 1957.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright, oval-shaped object with flashing lights.
The object moved slowly across the sky from west to east.
The sighting lasted for about 10 minutes.
The witnesses were a young husband and wife.
No further investigation was warranted, and the case was classified as 'UNIDENTIFIED'.
